;; Regression: resolving a dotted name whose head is a builtin (e.g.
;; `set.s`) drove ray_link_has to read the SLICE/HAS_LINK attribute bits of
;; a function object and dereference its slice_parent union field as if it
;; were a vector column — a garbage read / crash.  ray_link_has now returns
;; false for non-vector values, so the dotted lookup falls through to a
;; clean "undefined" name error.  Found by the eval fuzz target.
set.s !- name
sum.x !- name
count.y !- name

;; A real linked-column deref path is unaffected (plain names still resolve).
(+ 1 2) -- 3
